result.execSummary:
The defendant Faye Lyn Martin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
No possession or consumption of alcohol & no entering upon any bars or taverns.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Faye Lyn Martin, in custody, in court with attorney William Allen Dickens.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:05 PM. Called 15CF9 & 15CF34. State makes mention of different alias' for the defendant. Dickens has revocation summary, has no inaccuracies to report, believes defendant has 106 days credit. Defendant was convicted on counts #1 and #2 on 15CF09 and counts #1 and #4 on 15CF34. State makes final argument prior to recommendation. Court stops State and corrects error in the revocation paperwork in regards to maximum sentence. State continues - recommends 9 months on each count on 15CF09 - consecutive to each other and on 15CF24 - 9 months on count #4 and 6 months on count #1 - concurrent to each other but consecutive to 15CF09, entitled to 106 days credit (stipulated). Dickens makes final argument prior to recommendation - recommends time served or relatively short (3 month) concurrent sentence with treatment day-for-day. Martin makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF09 - count #1 - 6 months in FC jail, #2 - 6 months in FC jail - consecutive to count #1; 15CF34 - count #1 - 6 months in FC jail, count #4 - 9 months in FC jail - concurrent to each other but consecutive to count #2 in 15CF09, credit for 106 days, huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3), jail time can be served in another county if OK with Sheriff(s), turn any unpaid fines into civil judgments, right to appeal, adjourned.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on March 23, 2016 at 01:45 pm.

Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:33 PM. Also called 15CF34. Court has plea questionnaire. State - 15CF09 - amend #1 to misd BJ contrary to 946.49(1)(a) - G/NC plea to amended #1 and #2 as alleged, withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months each count - consecutive to Vilas County Case #14CF141 with conditons of: AODA, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars, employment/school, 100 hours of community service (total for the case), costs on each count; 15CF34 - amend count #1 to 450.11(7)(h) (possession of prescription without a valid prescription) - plead G/NC to amended count #1 and to count #4 as alleged, DRI #2 & #3, place on probation for 18 months, concurrent to 15CF09 and consecutive to Vilas County Case 14CF141, with same conditions except take all meds as prescribed, 100 hours of community service total - consecutive to CS on 15CF09. Burns and Martin agree. Court -15CF34 - amends count #1 to possession of prescripton without a valid prescription contrary to 450.11(7)(h) - reads new charge and penalty, Martin pleads NC to amended #1 and to #4 as alleged, Court dismisses and reads in counts #2 and #3; Court - 15CF09 - amend #1 to misd BJ contrary to 946.49(1)(a) - reads new charge and penalty, Martin pleads NC to amended count #1 and to count #2 as alleged. Court has plea questionnare, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Burns - follow joint recommendation - asks for 50 days credit. Martin withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF09 - counts #1 and #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months, concurrent to each other but consecutive to sentence she is serving on Vilas County Case #14CF141, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 100 hours of community service (total for the case) - to be completed within the first 6 months, costs on each count - paid thru probation; 15CF34 - counts #1 and #4 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months - concurrent to each other and concurrent to 15CF09, with same conditions except: additional 100 hours of community service (total on the case) - to be completed within the first 6 months - consecutive to community service on 15CF09, costs on each count - paid thru probation, no credit granted but can address it in the future if she is not given credit in her Vilas County Case, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:14 PM. Also called 15CF34. State - believe both PH's are being waived today, no promises under 15CF09 but has made a promise of no felony conviction if settled before trial on 15CF34. Burns and Martin agree. State files Information for both cases that mirror complaints. Court has waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her right to PH, binds over for trial, will proceed to ARGN. Burns has both Information, waives reading of both of them, enters NG plea to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond on both cases, set both matters for FPT.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 15, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Faye Lyn Martin in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:44 AM. Burns does have both complaints but just learned this AM of the new charges (15CF34). 15CF09 - Burns waives reading of complaint, requests PH. State - bond - $1000.00 cash bond. Burns - no objections. Court - 15CF09 - $500 cash bond - no consumption of alcohol, set for PH. 15CF34 - court reads charges and penalties. Martin understands charges and penalties. Burns waives further reading, requests PH, set for same date and time as other case (3/18/15 at 1:45 PM). State - bond - $500 cash bond. Burns - no objections. Court - bond - $500 cash bond, no consumption of alcohol.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 18, 2015 at 01:45 pm.

Defendant Faye Lyn Martin not in court.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:22 AM. State - S&C were mailed out and returned. court issues arrest warrant, body or $1000.
